Troubleshooting
Issue: Permission denied publickey
Solution:
Used correct username ubuntu
Verified key pair
Used bastion host to connect private EC2 instances

Issue: Only one server response showing from Load Balancer
Root cause:
One target was unhealthy in Target Group
Solution:
Started Python HTTP server on port 8000
Updated Security Group inbound rule
Verified Target Group health status

Cleanup
To avoid AWS Free Tier or unexpected charges:
Stop EC2 instances when not in use.
Delete Application Load Balancer.
Delete NAT Gateway if created.
Release unused Elastic IPs.
Delete unused EBS volumes and snapshots.

Key Learnings
Created a secure VPC architecture with public and private subnets.
Used bastion host to access private EC2 instances.
Configured Application Load Balancer with Target Group.
Troubleshot Target Group health check failures.
Understood Security Group rules for ALB-to-EC2 communication.
Learned AWS cleanup best practices to avoid unnecessary charges.

